John son of the reeve of Seamer was seen in company with poachers for the purpose of poaching. F ined 10³.

Nicholas Harel and Thomas Boye (both deceased) and eight strangers on the feast of St. Thomas killed two harts in the forest at Blackleys gate3 but where they took the game no one knows. Nothing done.

William son of Thomas of Egton, William Thumb of Trollesdale⁴ (fined elsewhere), and Roger de Hutton were accustomed to poach in Scalby Hay. Roger is put in exigent, and William son of Thomas of Egton is fined at Whitby.

William de Boyvill (deceased), Walter de Grendale (deceased), Adam de Upleatham (put in exigent), and William the Archer (in- dicted elsewhere), on the Thursday before Palm Sunday killed a hind and carried it to John Mortimer of Egton, Constable of Scarborough Castle (deceased). Nothing done.
